Interface ItemFrame

  • All Superinterfaces:

    public interface ItemFrame
extends CloneableEntity<ItemFrame>
    Represents an Item Frame. See Item Frame on the Minecraft Wiki.

    • Method Detail

      • getDisplayedItem

        Exceptional<Item> getDisplayedItem()
        Returns the current Item displayed in the item frame, wrapped in a Exceptional. If no item is currently being represented, Exceptional.none() is returned.
        Returns:
        The Item displayed in the item frame, or Exceptional.none().

      • setDisplayedItem

        void setDisplayedItem(Item stack)
        Sets the Item to be displayed in the item frame. If the item is equal to MinecraftItems.getAir() the displayed item is reset to display none.
        Parameters:
        stack - The Item to display.

      • getRotation

        ItemFrame.Rotation getRotation()
        Gets the ItemFrame.Rotation of the currently displayed Item. If no item is displayed, ItemFrame.Rotation.TOP is returned.
        Returns:
        The ItemFrame.Rotation of the displayed Item, or ItemFrame.Rotation.TOP.

      • setRotation

        void setRotation(ItemFrame.Rotation rotation)
        Sets the ItemFrame.Rotation of the currently displayed Item. If no item is displayed, the rotation is stored for the next item which will be represented.
        Parameters:
        rotation - The ItemFrame.Rotation of the displayed Item.

      • getBlockFace

        BlockFace getBlockFace()
        Gets the BlockFace the item frame is placed against. If no blockface is configured, BlockFace.NONE is returned.
        Returns:
        The BlockFace the item frame is placed against, or BlockFace.NONE.

      • setBlockFace

        void setBlockFace(BlockFace blockFace)
        Sets the BlockFace the item frame should be placed against.
        Parameters:
        blockFace - The BlockFace the item frame should be placed against.
